ature and elucidating its presence in both individual authors' lives and the genre of autobiographical fiction, The Awakening of Modern Japanese Fiction demonstrates a more nuanced understanding of the role of Buddhism in the development of Japanese modernity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aBuddhism and literaturezJapan. 0aBuddhism in literature. 0aBuddhist literaturexHistory and criticism. 0aJapanese fictionyTaishō period, 1912-1926xHistory and criticism. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Studies. 4aAsian Studies : Japanese Studies. 4aLiterature : Literary Criticism. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Buddhism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Asian / Japanese.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848143240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438481432423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438481432/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles